copy Https url from git website and clone it in ur local desktop
cmd 1 : git clone <url>
ex: $ git clone https://github.com/sravankaripe/Gits-Commands.git
    $ cd Gits-Commands/
    $ vi commands
    $ git status

to move file from current working directory to staging area
cmd 2 : git add <filename>
ex: $ git add commands
    $ git status
    
to move file from staging area to Repository(local repository)
cmd 3 : git commit -m "add a message"
ex: $ git commit -m "cmd 1 is added with some desc"
    $ git status
    
to move file from local repository to remote
cmd 4 : git pull
Note : before pushing always do pull
cmd 5 : git push
ex: $ git push [-a]
    $ git status

addtional commands need to know
-------------------------------
$git diff
to see the changes made

$git branch <branchName>
Ex: git branch Mybranch
to create branch 
$git checkout Mybranch

$git branched -merged 

$git merge Mybranch

to remove files from staging area 
$git reset

we can see log to see recent commits
$git log

to view informatiom about the remote repository
$git remote -v
$git branch -a 






